{"version":3,"term":{"cols":140,"rows":42,"type":"xterm-kitty"},"timestamp":1782087611,"command":"./cli/showcase-topology","title":"Topology & Hierarchy Showcase (read-only)","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/bash"}}
[0.004844, "o", "\u001b[1mPlatform Topology & vCluster Models Showcase (read-only, live)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.00185, "o", "\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n \u001b[1m1. The Root cluster is the hypervisor AND hosts vClusters (MODEL 1)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000083, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m The physical HA k3s cluster wears two hats at once: it runs KubeVirt (so it is the VM hypervisor) and it also runs tenant vClusters directly on itself (centralized).\r\n\r\n"]
[1.501789, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m Physical cluster nodes (the substrate):\r\n"]
[0.210632, "o", "      srv-pi-rack1          Ready   <none>                      30d    v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.65    <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS   6.8.0-1053-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n      srv-pi-rack2a         Ready   <none>                      30d    v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.40    <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.1 LTS   6.8.0-1053-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n"]
