[0.000049, "o", "      srv-rk1-nvme-04       Ready   <none>                      30d    v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.54    <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.1 LTS   6.1.0-1025-rockchip   containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n      srv-super6c-01-nvme   Ready   control-plane,etcd,worker   31d    v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.120   <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS   6.8.0-1053-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n"]
[0.000121, "o", "      srv-super6c-02-nvme   Ready   control-plane,etcd,worker   3d2h   v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.121   <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS   6.8.0-1053-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n      srv-super6c-04-nvme   Ready   control-plane,etcd,worker   3d1h   v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.122   <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS   6.8.0-1047-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n      srv-super6c-05-emmc   Ready   <none>                      3d     v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.124   <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS   6.8.0-1051-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n"]
[0.000039, "o", "      srv-super6c-06-emmc   Ready   <none>                      3d     v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.123   <none>   Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS   6.8.0-1053-raspi      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n"]
[0.000076, "o", "      srv-t7910             Ready   <none>                      9d     v1.35.5+k3s1   192.168.178.90    <none>   Ubuntu 26.04 LTS     7.0.0-22-generic      containerd://2.2.3-k3s1\r\n"]
[0.004083, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000011, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m KubeVirt virtualization engine running on the substrate:\r\n"]
[0.145294, "o", "      virt-handler-jz9lq   1/1   Running   102 (8h ago)   2d23h   10.0.6.222   srv-t7910   <none>   <none>\r\n"]
[0.007967, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m srv-t7910 is the KubeVirt hypervisor — and (see §4) the same cluster also hosts vClusters.\r\n"]
[0.000058, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000053, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n \u001b[1m2. A management cluster creates whole host clusters as KubeVirt VMs (MODEL 2)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000045, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000344, "o", " \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m Crossplane v2 (HostCluster XR) + Cluster API (CAPI) + provider-KubeVirt (CAPK) declaratively turn a one-file request into a full Kubernetes cluster whose NODES are VMs.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.501622, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m KubeVirt VMs backing the guest clusters (these ARE the cluster nodes):\r\n"]
[0.137104, "o", "      host-euw1-control-plane-gw2k6   10.0.6.132   <none>   Running\r\n      host-euw1-md-0-lvzrh-8twht      10.0.6.123   <none>   Running\r\n      host-mgmt-control-plane-6g64b   10.0.6.182   <none>   Running\r\n      host-mgmt-md-0-8x9kw-cm7fx      10.0.6.188   <none>   Running\r\n"]
[0.00417, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m Crossplane HostCluster XRs → composed into CAPI Clusters:\r\n"]
[0.126756, "o", "      host-euw1   regional     eu-west1   calico-vxlan   True\r\n      host-mgmt   management              calico-vxlan   True\r\n"]
[0.003986, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.144742, "o", "      host-euw1   Provisioned   true   true\r\n      host-mgmt   Provisioned   true   true\r\n"]
[0.004291, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m Each row is a real Kubernetes cluster whose control-plane/worker nodes are VMs on srv-t7910.\r\n"]
[0.000012, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000107, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000006, "o", " \u001b[1m3. Each host runs its OWN ArgoCD + its OWN vClusters (MODELS 3 & 4)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000089, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000037, "o", " \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m Decentralized GitOps: the management ArgoCD only creates clusters; each created host (role=management) gets its own ArgoCD (via CAAPH) seeded with a region-root, and provisions ITS region's vClusters locally — no central SPOF. A host promoted to management is the 'management-child' rung.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.722292, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m Management-role clusters (each runs its own ArgoCD):\r\n"]
[1.633231, "o", "      \u001b[35mhost-mgmt\u001b[0m (region=none) → local ArgoCD apps: 1\r\n"]
[0.000012, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m ArgoCD is sharded per cluster — the management plane is not a single point of failure.\r\n"]
[0.000101, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000028, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.00001, "o", " \u001b[1m4. vCluster placement — centralized (Root) vs decentralized (regional)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000075, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000007, "o", " \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m The SAME tenant chart (vCluster + Postgres + api + web + quota + netpol) runs either directly on the Root (centralized) or inside a regional host (decentralized). Same contract, different placement.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.501596, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m CENTRALIZED vClusters (running directly on the Root cluster):\r\n"]
[0.141603, "o", "      • vcluster-tenant-a-acceptance\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-a-dev\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-a-prod\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-b-dev\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-c-dev\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-x-dev\r\n      • vcluster-tenant-y-dev\r\n"]
[0.003623, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000107, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m DECENTRALIZED vClusters (inside each regional host, queried via jump pod):\r\n"]
[1.066203, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m Tenants are sharded across regional host VMs — the decentralized fleet model.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000094, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n \u001b[1m5. Variants validated: HA control plane & per-cluster CNI experiments\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000024, "o", " \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m On the same substrate we A/B-tested control-plane HA (etcd quorum) and three CNIs. On nested KubeVirt the per-VM masquerade interfered with cross-VM overlay traffic (IPIP/Cilium); Calico-VXLAN is what we validated end-to-end (README §3.1 — framed as an experiment, not a verdict).\r\n\r\n"]
[1.501771, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m Control-plane replicas per cluster (HA = 3 → etcd quorum 2/3):\r\n"]
[0.152318, "o", "      host-euw1-control-plane   1     1     true\r\n      host-mgmt-control-plane   1     1     true\r\n"]
[0.006989, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000022, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m CNI chosen per cluster (the experiment knob, spec.cni):\r\n"]
[0.20269, "o", "      host-euw1   calico-vxlan\r\n      host-mgmt   calico-vxlan\r\n"]
[0.004488, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m CNI is a per-cluster field; multi-VM clusters standardized on calico-vxlan after the experiment.\r\n"]
[0.000014, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000077, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n \u001b[1m6. Recursion: host-mgmt creates a child AND gives it its OWN stack (MODEL 6)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000047, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[1m═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000054, "o", " \u001b[33mℹ️ Concept:\u001b[0m host-mgmt is not just a workload host — it runs FULL CAPI+CAAPH and creates ITS OWN host cluster (mgmt-child), then delivers it the SAME stack the Root gives its regionals (ArgoCD + region-root + CNI), one rung down. mgmt-child ends up decentralized (own ArgoCD, no SPOF) hosting its own tenant vCluster. Whole chain validated CLEAN-ROOM (deleted everything, rebuilt from git).\r\n\r\n"]
[1.50203, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m host-mgmt runs CAPI + CAAPH (providers Ready — incl. addon=helm, so it installs ArgoCD on its OWN children):\r\n"]
[1.171437, "o", "      coreprovider.operator.cluster.x-k8s.io/cluster-api ready=True\r\n      bootstrapprovider.operator.cluster.x-k8s.io/kubeadm ready=True\r\n      controlplaneprovider.operator.cluster.x-k8s.io/kubeadm ready=True\r\n      infrastructureprovider.operator.cluster.x-k8s.io/kubevirt ready=True\r\n      addonprovider.operator.cluster.x-k8s.io/helm ready=True\r\n"]
[0.000541, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000053, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m host-mgmt CREATED a child cluster (mgmt-child); its VMs run on the ROOT's KubeVirt (via external-infra):\r\n"]
[1.025035, "o", "      default   mgmt-child         Provisioned   4h53m   \r\n"]
[0.150415, "o", "      mgmt-child-control-plane-dbhws   10.0.6.13    Running\r\n      mgmt-child-md-0-pr2jw-jttlf      10.0.6.147   Running\r\n"]
[0.004497, "o", "\r\n"]
[1.389366, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m RECURSION: mgmt-child got its OWN ArgoCD + region-root FROM host-mgmt (decentralized, no central SPOF):\r\n"]
[1.099438, "o", "      ArgoCD pods Running on mgmt-child: 7\r\n"]
[1.149429, "o", "      app: region-root Synced Healthy\r\n      app: vcluster-tenant-z-dev Synced Healthy\r\n      app: wl-tenant-z-dev Synced Healthy\r\n"]
[0.012176, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000039, "o", "  \u001b[34m•\u001b[0m and mgmt-child hosts its OWN tenant vCluster (the recursion's leaf — pg/api/web run INSIDE it):\r\n"]
[1.086869, "o", "      • vcluster-tenant-z-dev\r\n"]
[0.005233, "o", "  \u001b[32m✔\u001b[0m Root → host-mgmt (mgmt) → mgmt-child (regional, OWN ArgoCD) → vcluster-tenant-z. Full recursion, 100% GitOps (clean-room rebuilt).\r\n\r\n\u001b[32m\u001b[1m✔ TOPOLOGY & MODELS SHOWCASE COMPLETE\u001b[0m\r\nSame homelab, every model: hypervisor+host (1), mgmt creates clusters (2), decentralized\r\n"]
[0.00001, "o", "regional ArgoCD (3,4), HA + CNI variants (5), and RECURSION (6: host-mgmt → mgmt-child w/ own ArgoCD → vcluster).\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000278, "x", "0"]
